DevOps List of Training Websites

Do not DARE attempting to get into DevOps and you have no comfort in Linux and you lack understanding of technical and networking fundamentals. Make 100% sure you learn first! DevOps is not for absolute beginners:

Free (All IT Professionals Changing Positions or Careers):
Technical Fundamentals: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLTk5ZYSbd9Mh1mxFFu1Jx-g9VsdzQ0REW
Networking Fundamentals: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLTk5ZYSbd9Mi_ya5tVFD8NFfU1YZOyml1
60 Important Linux Commands: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gd7BXuUQ91w

Paid (Beginners to IT):
TechWorld with Nana: https://www.techworld-with-nana.com/it-beginners-course
Coursera & Google: https://www.coursera.org/professional-certificates/google-it-support 

Free:
Udemy: https://www.udemy.com/course/learn-git-and-github-over-the-weekend (Git)
Udemy: https://www.udemy.com/course/git-started-with-github (Git)
Google: https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/journeys/76 (DevOps)
Google: https://www.cloudskillsboost.google/journeys/20 (SRE Focused DevOps)
FreeCodeCamp: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j5Zsa_eOXeY
TechniesCamp: https://techiescamp.com/ (Some Paid Course Options)

Paid:
Udemy: https://www.udemy.com/course/the-complete-devops-bootcamp (DevOps)
KodeKloud: https://kodekloud.com/courses/devops-pre-requisite-course/ (DevOps)
Linux Foundation: https://training.linuxfoundation.org/training/devops-bootcamp/ 
TechWorld with Nana: https://www.techworld-with-nana.com/devops-bootcamp
AOS Notes: https://www.aosnote.com/store
SimpliLearn: https://www.simplilearn.com/devops (India Based)
ClarusWay: https://clarusway.com/devops/ (High Cost)
UT Dallas: https://bootcamp.utdallas.edu/programs/ 
Clarusway: https://clarusway.com/aws-devops/
LevelUpInTech: https://www.levelupintech.com/
Amazon AWS: https://aws.amazon.com/training/restart/ (AWS Specific)
Adrian Cantrill: https://learn.cantrill.io?affcode=212820_n7shpfjf (AWS Specific)
Neal Davis: https://digitalcloud.training/cloud-mastery-bootcamp/?utm_source=megamenu&utm_medium=image&utm_campaign=bootcamps (AWS Specific)


(Disclaimer: College/University Certificate programs will not impact or help get a job. The Industry IT certification, projects and experience is what will help you. Don't get scammed!)


Common platforms or software used in DevOps:
Linux (Red Hat Enterprise Linux, Debian, Ubuntu)
Vagrant
Docker
Kubernetes
Jenkins
Terraform
Ansible

Monitoring:
Prometheus
Grafana

Remote Video or Chat Communications:
Slack
Teams
Google Meet

CLI Editors:
Visual Studio Code

Code Repositories:
GitHub
Gitlab

Local OS Editors:
VIM (Pro Tip: There will be times when you cannot get to any form of GUI, but VI will always be available since it's embedded in the OS. So learn it.)
Terminator (Linux/Mac)

Human Interaction:
Soft-Skills, Advanced Typing and Verbal Communication Skills, Listening Skills, Empathy

Projects:
https://github.com/acantril/learn-cantrill-io-labs/tree/master

Collaboration & Community:
https://devopsdays.org/
https://devops.com/ (FYI. Clunky and Busy Website)


